A group of masked clowns attacked a young man's face with cavity filler during a terrifying Halloween prank.

Michael Day feared he would lose his sight after the reckless pranksters sprayed the quick-drying filler over his face as he was walking home from a party in Southend-on-Sea, Essex, on Saturday.

The 21-year-old initially thought he had been struck was shaving foam but began to panic when it began to solidify around his face, fusing his eyes together.  

