His mother Lyn Day is urging witnesses to come forward so she can track down her son's attackers.

She said: 'When he arrived he was covered in the cavity filler. It was all over his clothes and hair.

'As we tried to get the foam off it was taking parts of his skin with it and it looked as though the chemicals were burning his skin.

'I just want to warn people that this has been going on.'

Anyone with information about the incident should call Southend police on 101.

 

